{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Strip Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Strip Filter</h1>

<p>Removes leading and trailing whitespace from a string. Whitespace includes spaces, tabs, newlines, and carriage returns.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "  hello  " | strip %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Related Filters</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>strip</strong> — Remove whitespace from both ends</li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/lstrip"><strong>lstrip</strong></a> — Remove whitespace from the left (leading) end only</li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/rstrip"><strong>rstrip</strong></a> — Remove whitespace from the right (trailing) end only</li>
</ul>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "  hello  " | strip %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> hello</p>
<p>Spaces on both sides are removed.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "\t  indented line\n" | strip %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> indented line</p>
<p>Tabs (<code>\t</code>) and newlines (<code>\n</code>) are also stripped, not just spaces.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "  leading only" | lstrip %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> leading only</p>
<p>Use <code>lstrip</code> to strip only the left side, preserving trailing whitespace. Use <code>rstrip</code> for the right side only.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li><code>strip</code> removes all leading and trailing whitespace as defined by Go's <code>strings.TrimSpace</code>: spaces (<code> </code>), horizontal tabs (<code>\t</code>), newlines (<code>\n</code>), vertical tabs (<code>\v</code>), form feeds (<code>\f</code>), carriage returns (<code>\r</code>), NEL (U+0085), and NBSP (U+00A0).</li>
  <li>Whitespace in the middle of the string is never affected.</li>
  <li>Use <code>lstrip</code> or <code>rstrip</code> when you only want to trim one side.</li>
</ul>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/lstrip">lstrip</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/rstrip">rstrip</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
